  {
    "direction": null,
    "comprehension": null,
    "content": "<p>An L-shaped elastic member ABC with slender arms AB and BC of uniform crosssection&nbsp;is clamped at end A and connected to a pin at end C. The pin remains in&nbsp;continuous contact with and is constrained to move in a smooth horizontal slot. The&nbsp;section modulus of the member is same in both the arms. The end C is subjected to&nbsp;a horizontal force P and all the deflections are in the plane of the figure. Given the&nbsp;length AB is 4a and length BC is 𝑎, the magnitude and direction of the normal force&nbsp;on the pin from the slot, respectively, are</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzqiwkif/ccfdb834-36a2-428e-9516-1f04050daf21/7f2a9e70-5867-11ef-94af-39d5f0b54eb8/file-jaoe38c1lzqiwkig.webp?format=webp\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lzqiwkif/ccfdb834-36a2-428e-9516-1f04050daf21/7f2a9e70-5867-11ef-94af-39d5f0b54eb8/file-jaoe38c1lzqiwkig.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ME 2022 Set 1 Strength of Materials - Deflection of Beams Question 2 English\">",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "3𝑃/8, and downwards"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "5𝑃/8, and upwards"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "𝑃/4, and downwards"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "3𝑃/4, and upwards"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "explanation": "<p><b>Deflection in x-direction due to load P :</b></p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzqizie9/cdce65bf-0541-46ac-85b1-742a1e6bfe83/d0f5a510-5867-11ef-94af-39d5f0b54eb8/file-jaoe38c1lzqiziea.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lzqizie9/cdce65bf-0541-46ac-85b1-742a1e6bfe83/d0f5a510-5867-11ef-94af-39d5f0b54eb8/file-jaoe38c1lzqiziea.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ME 2022 Set 1 Strength of Materials - Deflection of Beams Question 2 English Explanation 1\">\n\n<p>The deflection at point C, $\\Delta C_1$, in the x-direction due to load P is :</p>\n\n<p>$$\\Delta C_1 = \\frac{P a (4a)^2}{2EI} = \\frac{8 P a^3}{EI}$$ .......... (i)</p>\n\n<p><b>Deflection in y-direction due to load P :</b></p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzqizezi/ea881a75-46e3-44e9-9b1c-51ad1a7a7b63/ce535be0-5867-11ef-94af-39d5f0b54eb8/file-jaoe38c1lzqizezj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lzqizezi/ea881a75-46e3-44e9-9b1c-51ad1a7a7b63/ce535be0-5867-11ef-94af-39d5f0b54eb8/file-jaoe38c1lzqizezj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ME 2022 Set 1 Strength of Materials - Deflection of Beams Question 2 English Explanation 2\">\n\n<p>The deflection at point C, $\\Delta C_2$, in the y-direction due to load P is :</p>\n\n<p>$$\\Delta C_2 = \\frac{F (4a)^3}{3EI} = \\frac{64 F a^3}{3EI}$$ .......... (ii)</p>\n\n<p>Equating equations (i) and (ii) :</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\frac{8 P a^3}{EI} = \\frac{64 a^3 F}{3EI}$$</p>\n\n<p>Solving for F :</p>\n\n<p>$$F = \\frac{3P}{8}$$</p>\n\n<p>The force F is directed downwards. Thus, the correct option is (A).</p>",
    "answer": null,
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "gate-me-2022-set-1",
    "difficulty": null
  },
